snippet: Bronislaw Komorowski, the center-right incumbent, came in second to the conservative Andrzej Duda in the first round of the election, a stunning result in a closely watched race.
abstract: Conservative Andrzej Duda of Poland will challenge Pres Bronislaw Komorowski in runoff election after winning 34.8 percent of vote in first round of balloting; results are setback for ruling center-right party and could indicate major political change in upcoming parliamentary elections.

byline.original: By RICK LYMAN and JOANNA BERENDT

lead_paragraph: Bronislaw Komorowski, the center-right incumbent, came in second to the conservative Andrzej Duda in the first round of the election, a stunning result in a closely watched race.

headline.main: Polish Presidential Election Heads for Runoff
headline.print_headline: President of Poland Has Setback in Balloting
